 The three-day sessions at the 10th BRICS Academic Forum have come to an end. The intellectuals that gathered have agreed on 20 socio-economic resolutions which they plan to present to the BRICS leaders ahead of the summit. CNBC Africa’s Rofhiwa Madzena spoke to South Africa’s representative delegate, Professor Ari Sitas.
